parseFrom

public int parseFrom(java.lang.String s,
                     int start)
              throws FBDataTypeException
Parses the receiver's content from the given String. The character at the start position must be a double quote ("), and parsing will proceed up to the next double quote. Note that a WSTRING parsed this way can't contain a double quote).

Overrides:
parseFrom in class ANY
Parameters:
s - The String from which to parse the content.
start - The character position from which to begin parsing.
Returns:
The character position following the terminating double quote.
Throws:
FBDataTypeException - INVALID_OBJECT - The field had invalid syntax or no terminator was found.
See Also:
ANY.NULL_OBJECT, FBDataTypeException.invalidObject(String)
